title.7: Marvel Super Hero Contest of Champions (1982) #1

description.3: The Enchantress kidnaps Dazzler and places her under her thrall! But what about Alison’s new relationship with Kenneth Barnett?
description.5: The galactic herald returns in this jam-packed one-shot! Silver Surfer recalls happier times with the Fantastic Four. With Norrin Radd becoming a distant memory with each passing day, will Surfer ever recover the man he once was? Surfer returns to his homeland Zenn-La to find absolute devastation. A new quest begins for Silver Surfer -- one that involves finding his soulmate, Shalla Bal!
description.7: Elders of the Universe Grandmaster and 'The Unknown' use their control over time and space to "BAMF!" ALL of Earth's heroes to the arena of Champions! Every living being on Earth is now held in suspended animation - and they'll remain that way unless Marvel's super heroes agree to take part in the "Contest"! Check out this unbelievably fun read!
description.8: Shanna seeks vengeance for the man she loves—Mele! Ka-Zar stands accused of murder.
description.13: Rogue Squadron infiltrates an Imperial outpost!
description.16: Nighthawk and Valkyrie have fallen, and the Defenders are devastated to lose their friends. So when hope arises that Valkyrie can be saved, the team jumps at the chance...but so does the Enchantress!
description.18: More secret tales of the Marvel U! Spider-Man, Angel and Ka-Zar brave the Savage Land, Mr. Fantastic clashes with Annihilus, and the quest of Marvel editor Al Milgrom continues in "Editori-Al"!
description.19: Will Spider-Woman: Jessica Drew help Alison Blaire find her mother? If not, Dazzler may play detective herself.
description.20: Matt can't bring himself to believe that Elektra is truly gone and so proceeds to dig up her grave. Meanwhile, Punisher breaks out from prison.
description.21: The Hulk finds himself on Halfworld, a strange planet full of talking animals.
description.22: Iron Man discovers power outages right above Cougar Mountain, after his suit powers down mid-flight. What does Sonny's "Mom" have to do with it? Meanwhile, Mrs. Arbogast continues to juggle duties at Stark International.
description.23: Donald Blake is in Chicago giving a medical seminar. But that doesn't mean Thor's exempt from a battle or two!
description.24: The Fantastic Four's Christmas plans take a turn for the worse when Terrax crashes the festivities! Guest-starring the Mighty Thor, the Amazing Spider-Man, and a whole slew of your favorite heroes!
description.25: Whose side is the Imperial Guard on and what mystery has been hatched on the Shi'ar homeworld?
description.27: Mele and Ka-Zar “bond” on a hunting trip while hashing out their mutual feelings for Shanna.
description.28: A man lies dead due to an attack by spiders. What is the connection to Spider-Man? An unusual and "offbeat" mystery that may just leave Spider fans with more questions than answers!
description.29: Moondragon summons the remaining four Avengers after getting into trouble with a galactic warlord. Now, the Avengers find themselves in deep space, and deep trouble, with the inhabitants of the planet Ba-Bani!
description.30: It's Team America in this all-new action-packed issue! Captain America teams up with the new motorcycle stunt performers, Team America, to stop the Mad Thinker from kidnapping the world's Nobel Peace Prize Winners!
description.31: Luke and Lando look to purchase black market TIE fighters, but then a large worm-like creature known as a Watchbeast attacks!
description.41: The Defenders race against time to stop a sinister plot that involves using the world's psychics to incite World War III! But to save the Earth, which Defenders must pay the ultimate price?
description.42: Will the Thing have any sympathy for Sandman while he's down on his luck and mentally unwell? As the Sandman weeps of his past to the Thing at a local bar, Grimm wrestles with whether or not the villain's sentiments are genuine.
description.44: Upon returning to the present from 1943's London, Morgana falls into an unexpected coma. Seeking answers, Strange's astral form transports itself to the Spanish Inquisition…where he encounters the terrifying Nightmare.
description.45: Dazzler and her band land an opening gig, but an assassination attempt during showtime sends She-Hulk barreling into the picture!
description.46: "One Wins. One Dies." The cover's text immediately lets you know something big is going down this issue. And Frank Miller's badass imagery drives the point home.
description.47: It's Iron Man versus alien spores! While overseeing an outer-space shipment for Stark International, Tony comes face to face with these malignant, and mysterious, galactic foes.
description.49: Loki uses his powers to control the legendary Easter Island heads! Can our hero Thor outsmart his half-brother?
description.50: What if Earth's Mightiest were killed by Michael Korvac? His omnipotence has toppled the Avengers, spelling doom for every super hero. This is the reign of Korvac- undeterred!
description.51: The FF travel to Africa to visit an ancient site with their ally, Black Panther. Will Sue be the key to overcoming their new foe, Emperor Gaius Tiberius?
description.52: Can the X-Men and Starjammers combined drive back the Brood warriors?
description.54: Ka-Zar and Shanna get lost from each other in the mysterious jungles of Pangea!
description.55: When a malfunction threatens the Rebel fleet, it will be up to the droids to save the day!
description.56: It's difficult for Spider-Man to take down the Black Cat. Especially when his heart is involved. An emotional and wrenching battle that Spider-Man doesn't want to win!
description.57: The Avengers grant a young boy access to the mansion, assuming that he is an innocent fan. But when the boy commits suicide in front of the team, only to have his body disintegrate and re-form, the Avengers realize they have entered the realm of the supernatural!
description.58: Kyle Richmond, Gargoyle, Valkyrie and Hellcat of the Defenders have been captured by August Masters and his minions who have been manipulating psychics for his own goals. Can Cap save the day? Or will August Master conquer all?
description.66: The BEAST joins the Defenders! And he's not on the team long before they're thrust into the strange dimension of the Resurrection Stone! Plus, Daimon fights his inner AND outer demons as his satanic father tempts him to rule all of Hell! Guest-starring Mister Fantastic!
description.69: The debut of this classic series, featuring special stories from around the Marvel Universe! Featuring Spider-Man, Daredevil, and...the Marvel Bullpen!?
description.70: Dazzler's on trial for MURDER! Alison Blaire fends for herself in court to prove her innocence. To top it off, there's trouble brewing for Dazzler and Paul Jansen…
description.71: Using Ben Urich's lead, Daredevil hunts for Kingpin's wife. Plus, Foggy's life may be in danger...
description.72: Professional thief and part-time Ant-Man Scott Lang discovers the Mauler armor while stealing crates from Cord Conglomerate. Only Iron Man and War Machine have the tech to take him down!
description.73: Tony Stark's space shuttle is attacked by Man-Beast...and astronaut Diane Lamarr is trapped inside! Can Thor save Diane and the shuttle before Man-Beast returns to Counter-Earth?
description.74: Quicksilver seeks the aid of the Fantastic Four in the war on Attilian, and to help solve what mysterious illness is plaguing the Inhumans! Is this the end of the Inhuman Royal Family?
description.75: Cyclops learns that Corsair is his father, but there's no time for a family reunion as the Brood arrive.
description.76: The First Appearance of Cloak and Dagger! But Spider-Man learns that this vigilante duo has a very different approach to crime fighting.
description.79: Can Luke and the crew clear Cloud City of its Imperial infestation?
description.80: Ka-Zar enters the ninth level of the underworld to take on demon lord Belasco!
description.85: Fan-favorite Black Cat has returned...and she's baring her fangs and claws. Watch Spider-Man go up against the alluring Cat. Will Spidey be able to resist her natural charms?
description.86: Janet Van Dyne makes her triumphant return to the Avengers, and requests a position of leadership. Meanwhile, a disgraced Hank Pym agrees to create tech for an old arch nemesis. Enter Egghead, a dangerous criminal with mind-control powers!
description.87: When Captain America addresses a high school assembly, a student ridicules Cap's "false American Dream and tries to assassinate him. Has the nation lost faith in the Sentinel of Liberty? Will Cap America turn a blind eye to cracks in our nation?
description.90: Devil-Slayer is lured by Ian Fate when the villain threatens to kill his estranged wife, as revenge for when he killed Fate's wife and child so long ago. Things take an odd turn and an important life is lost in the crossfires…
description.91: The Death of Captain Marvel.  One of the poignant comics ever, Mar-vell succumbs to cancer in this classic and touching story.
description.94: Sir Baskerville holds Strange in his family's castle, where Nazi-sympathizer Viscount Heinrich Krowler grows in mystic might to conduct a hate-inducing spell!
description.95: All Dazzler wants is a job! And when she's offered a new gig, Alison immediately accepts. However, the job description didn't include fighting for her life…
description.96: The theatrical and over-dressed Foolkiller has sworn revenge on all "fools". With a villainous goal that vague, Spider-Man is sure to have his hands full. But who is the Foolkiller? And how is he connected to Peter Parker's past?
description.97: Secret identities are revealed when the Avengers are under the mercy of Molecule Man! The Silver Surfer must stand alone to save Earth's Mightiest Heroes!
description.98: The fight against the Sultan continues! When the heroes find themselves overwhelmed by the Sultan's evil forces, it's up to Peter Parker to use his genius intellect to save the world! Hey, I thought Cap was the star of this comic book!
description.99: Lando returns to Cloud City, but its now under Imperial rule!

0.text: Boomerang is back! And when he comes under the employ of one Wilson Fisk, the titantic Kingpin, Boomerang sets out to stop the Wall-Crawler!

1.text: She-Hulk and the Thing must team up to stop Negator!

3.text: The Enchantress kidnaps Dazzler and places her under her thrall! But what about Alison’s new relationship with Kenneth Barnett?

4.text: The climactic conclusion to Moon Knight vs. Arsenal! All looks lost, as Moon Knight is captured by Arsenal and his Third World Slayers. Luckily, a turn of events is in order. Will Arsenal’s ‘Manhattan Plan’ come to fruition? If it does, all of New York City will be up in flames!

5.text: The galactic herald returns in this jam-packed one-shot! Silver Surfer recalls happier times with the Fantastic Four. With Norrin Radd becoming a distant memory with each passing day, will Surfer ever recover the man he once was? Surfer returns to his homeland Zenn-La to find absolute devastation. A new quest begins for Silver Surfer -- one that involves finding his soulmate, Shalla Bal!

6.text: Power Man and Iron fist are trapped in the Royal Palace in Halwan where there’s a fight around every corner! Can the two get out of there before they become prisoners of war?!

10.text: Shang-Chi and his team finish their business in Toronto before turning their attention to a cache of diamonds in Africa.

15.text: Thing enters the microverse! After one of Reed's experiments goes awry, Ben Grimm is transported to the dimension of the very, very small. Only Scott Lang is available to answer the call of Ant-Man, shrinking down to particulate size to pull the Thing back to the other side!

16.text: Nighthawk and Valkyrie have fallen, and the Defenders are devastated to lose their friends. So when hope arises that Valkyrie can be saved, the team jumps at the chance...but so does the Enchantress!

19.text: Will Spider-Woman: Jessica Drew help Alison Blaire find her mother? If not, Dazzler may play detective herself.

26.text: Peter just wants to have a study date with Marcy Kane, but will sparks fly when Electro breaks out of prison?

32.text: Marlene goes undercover as one of Nimrod Strange’s bodyguards, while Moon Knight infiltrates his island base. Has Moon Knight resigned Marlene to a fate worse than death? Arsenal shows up, leaving Moon Knight in explosive straits!

33.text: Power Man and Iron Fist head to Halwan, where Abe Brown is under fire for crimes he has no memory of committing!

34.text: Shang-Chi and MI-6 finally go their separate ways.

38.text: The Fantastic Four have a bundle of laughs with the rest of the Marvel Universe! However, someone seems keen on ruining the party…

40.text: Hulk vanishes while battling the Galaxy Master! Later, Betty Ross saves Rick Jones’ life…

41.text: The Defenders race against time to stop a sinister plot that involves using the world's psychics to incite World War III! But to save the Earth, which Defenders must pay the ultimate price?

43.text: Dalia and Meru team up and take over Valkyrie’s mind to compel her to kill Spider-Man and Thor!

45.text: Dazzler and her band land an opening gig, but an assassination attempt during showtime sends She-Hulk barreling into the picture!

46.text: "One Wins. One Dies." The cover's text immediately lets you know something big is going down this issue. And Frank Miller's badass imagery drives the point home.

53.text: Calypso and Kraven are on the hunt…for Spider-Man!

59.text: Leiko and Shang-Chi continue to try and hunt down the Ghost Maker and stop the incoming acid rainstorm.

62.text: Moon Knight must thwart attacks from all sides after Nimrod Strange unleashes his three best assassins. But will they best Moon Knight? The Third World Slayers have no idea what’s coming for them!

63.text: Power Man and Iron Fist are hired by the offices of Murphy Merriam Fontaine to track down a robber responsible for break-ins.

65.text: Daydra, Empress of the Sagittarius System, recruits Hulk to take on the Galaxy Master!

66.text: The BEAST joins the Defenders! And he's not on the team long before they're thrust into the strange dimension of the Resurrection Stone! Plus, Daimon fights his inner AND outer demons as his satanic father tempts him to rule all of Hell! Guest-starring Mister Fantastic!

68.text: Donald Blake performs surgery on a woman named Dalia who is part of a revolution in Cherron. Guest-starring Spider-Man!

76.text: Check out the first appearance of street-level heroes Cloak and Dagger! But Spider-Man learns that this vigilante duo has a very different approach to crime fighting.

77.text: Marc Spector endures tragedy when a longtime friend is murdered in front of him. But Moon Knight will exact revenge! Moon Knight vs. The Master Sniper and his gang of hired guns.

78.text: Art imitates life in this strange, (and theatrical), issue!

81.text: Shang-Chi fights the Ghost Maker as he tries to thwart the KGB's latest attempt at tracking down the Dark Angel.

90.text: Devil-Slayer is lured by Ian Fate when the villain threatens to kill his estranged wife, as revenge for when he killed Fate's wife and child so long ago. Things take an odd turn and an important life is lost in the crossfires…

92.text: The Thing helps Alpha Flight take down Ranark!
